#: troubleshooting.xml:797
#, no-c-format
msgid "Valid User Name and Password Not Accepted"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:798
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is by far the most common problem users encounter, because there are many reasons this can occur. Depending on whether you use local user management and authentication or network authentication, login failures occur for different reasons."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:804
#, no-c-format
msgid "Local user management can fail for the following reasons:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:814
#, no-c-format
msgid "The user's home directory containing the desktop configuration files is corrupted or write protected."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:820
#, no-c-format
msgid "There may be problems with the X Window System authenticating this particular user, especially if the user's home directory has been used with another Linux distribution prior to installing the current one."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:827
#, no-c-format
msgid "To locate the reason for a local login failure, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:832
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check whether the user remembered his password correctly before you start debugging the whole authentication mechanism. If the user may not remember his password correctly, use the &yast; User Management module to change the user's password. Pay attention to the <keycap>Caps Lock</keycap> key and unlock it, if necessary."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:841
#, no-c-format
msgid "Log in as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> and check the system journal with <command>journalctl -e</command> for error messages of the login process and of PAM."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:848
#, no-c-format
msgid "Try to log in from a console (using <keycombo> <keycap function=\"control\"/> <keycap function=\"alt\"/> <keycap>F1</keycap> </keycombo> ). If this is successful, the blame cannot be put on PAM, because it is possible to authenticate this user on this machine. Try to locate any problems with the X Window System or the &gnome; desktop. For more information, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec.trouble.login.dk\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:895
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the following, common reasons a network authentication for a particular user may fail on a specific machine are listed:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:901
#, no-c-format
msgid "The user may have entered the wrong password."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:906
#, no-c-format
msgid "The user name exists in the machine's local authentication files and is also provided by a network authentication system, causing conflicts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:912
#, no-c-format
msgid "The home directory exists but is corrupt or unavailable. Perhaps it is write protected or is on a server that is inaccessible at the moment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:918
#, no-c-format
msgid "The user does not have permission to log in to that particular host in the authentication system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:924
#, no-c-format
msgid "The machine has changed host names, for whatever reason, and the user does not have permission to log in to that host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:930
#, no-c-format
msgid "The machine cannot reach the authentication server or directory server that contains that user's information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:936
#, no-c-format
msgid "There may be problems with the X Window System authenticating this particular user, especially if the user's home has been used with another Linux distribution prior to installing the current one."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:943
#, no-c-format
msgid "To locate the cause of the login failures with network authentication, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:949
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check whether the user remembered their password correctly before you start debugging the whole authentication mechanism."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: troubleshooting.xml:955
#, no-c-format
msgid "Determine the directory server which the machine relies on for authentication and make sure that it is up and running and properly communicating with the other machines."
